From: Eric Biggers <ebiggers@google.com>
Date: Mon, 5 May 2025 12:10:38 -0700
Subject: crypto: algif_aead - use memcpy_sglist() instead of null skcipher
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
Git-commit: f2804d0eee8ddd57aa79d0b82872b74c21e1b69b
References: bsc#1262573 CVE-2026-31431

For copying data between two scatterlists, just use memcpy_sglist()
instead of the so-called "null skcipher".  This is much simpler.

Signed-off-by: Eric Biggers <ebiggers@google.com>
Signed-off-by: Herbert Xu <herbert@gondor.apana.org.au>
[~nstange: adapt to skipped patches, most notably to
 c1abe6f570af ("crypto: af_alg: Use extract_iter_to_sg() to create
 scatterlists.")]
Acked-by: Nicolai Stange <nstange@suse.de>
---
 crypto/Kconfig      |    1 
 crypto/algif_aead.c |   99 +++++++++-------------------------------------------
 2 files changed, 18 insertions(+), 82 deletions(-)

--- a/crypto/Kconfig
+++ b/crypto/Kconfig
@@ -1845,7 +1845,6 @@ config CRYPTO_USER_API_AEAD
